<p><b>SCHOLARSHIPS AVAILABLE FOR CATHOLIC
SCHOOLS</b>. St. James has SIX Catholic Elementary
Schools in Seattle: St. Therese, St. Paul, St. Edward,
St. George, St. Joseph and Holy Family Bilingual.
These schools provide in-parish tuition rates for
registered St. James parishioners. We also support
FOUR Catholic High Schools (O’Dea, Holy Names,
Bishop Blanchet, and Kennedy Catholic) through the Simperman Scholar program. Please contact 
<a href="mailto:tvandeven@stjames-cathedral.org?subject=Scholarships for Catholic Schools">Theresa
Van de Ven</a> at 206-219-5822 for requirements and an application
packet for the 2020-2021 school year. Completed
applications must be submitted by April 30, 2020.</p>
<p><b>MATT TALBOT CENTER ST. PATRICK’S DINNER</b>. St.
James Cathedral is pleased to host this annual dinner,
which will be held on Sunday, March 15 in the
Cathedral Hall. It will feature Irish cultural
performances, former Prime Minister of Ireland Enda
Kenny, current Mayor of Galway Mike Cubbard, a
program member featured speaker, good food, and
good company! Online registration is open at 
<a target="_bulletin" href="https://www.mtcenter.org/event-info/st-patricks-dinner-1">https://www.mtcenter.org/event-info/st-patricks-dinner-1</a>.
Doors open at 5:45pm; program begins at 6:30pm;
dinner is from 7pm-9pm. Established in 1985, the Matt
Talbot Center is a recovery program and treatment
center for the addicted, the homeless and mentally ill.
Located in Belltown, the Matt Talbot Center offers
hope, services and support to individuals ready to
commit to their recovery. <i>Information</i>, 
<a href="mailto:zeldab@ccsww.org?subject=Matt Talboty Center St. Patrick's Dinner">Zelda Buck</a>, 206-707-6228.</p>

